{{Quote|The Rebels have infiltrated Hangar 85G, and are preparing to escape on one of the shuttles. Get to the hangar and take out that shuttle before it takes off.|An Imperial officer|<ref name="BFII">''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II]]''</ref>}}
'''Hangar 85G''' was a hangar bay inside the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first]] [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]], in operation during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. This hangar was located in proximity to the battle station's [[Superlaser Fire Control]] Room and [[Detention Block 2180]], along with [[Hangar 84G]].<ref name="BFII" />

Hangar 85G became a battleground when a number of [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] prisoners [[Death Star Uprising|escaped]] from their cells on the Death Star and attempted to flee the battle station. A group of would-be escapees, led by a [[Death Star prisoner|Jedi]], blasted its way into Hangar 85G, and commandeered a [[Sentinel-class landing craft/Legends|transport]]. However, the [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] of the [[501st Legion/Legends|501st Legion]] countered the prison break, killing the escapees including the Jedi. Hangar 85G was secured, and the threat passed.<ref name="BFII" />

Hangar 85G was destroyed, along with the Death Star itself, when it exploded during the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]].<ref name="Episode IV">{{Film|IV}}</ref>

